					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In case you can't watch videos where you are, AVGN's seven deadly sins of <em>Kid Kool</em> are<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>(3:22) Ratchet scrolling makes it hard to recover your weapon. </li><li>(3:44) Needing to run so fast to cross gaps that you can't react to lethal obstacles. </li><li>(4:05) Not enough space to accelerate to make jumps, combined with no mid-air acceleration. </li><li>(4:34) Time window to leap out of water after skipping over its surface is too short. </li><li>(5:13) Leaving the top or bottom of the screen freezes the game momentarily while an entire screen scrolls in. It's like SMB2's but worse; at least SMB2 only scrolled 60% at once. </li><li>(5:42) Invisible coin blocks interfere with jumping over enemies, like in the various platform-hell hacks of SMB1 and SMW. </li><li>(6:11) Leaps of faith to a screen below with potentially deadly hazards. </li></ol></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

